38:37.349 --> 38:40.352
La Caracola is a party space
on a strip of sand

38:40.387 --> 38:43.493
about ten minutes
outside of Jose Ignacio.

38:43.528 --> 38:46.703
The ocean on one side,
a lagoon on the other.

38:46.738 --> 38:48.360
During the high season,

38:48.395 --> 38:51.225
it's a regular hangout
for over-the-top asados.

38:51.259 --> 38:55.263
Today Nacho is supervising
a meal for a bunch of friends.

39:01.235 --> 39:03.686
Hey, guys.

39:13.903 --> 39:15.939
What's going on in here?

39:15.974 --> 39:18.252
Hey. How's it going?

39:18.286 --> 39:20.116
- Very good.
- So this is Martin.

39:20.150 --> 39:22.014
- Hey, how are you?
- How are you?

39:22.049 --> 39:24.845
Martin Pittaluga is
the co-owner of La Huella,

39:24.879 --> 39:26.364
a restaurant in town
that also serves

39:26.398 --> 39:28.227
as the mother ship
for this place.

39:28.262 --> 39:30.195
- Right?
- Man, what a spot.

39:30.229 --> 39:32.121
- I mean, you look at this...
- The weather is good?

39:32.128 --> 39:33.898
The weather is difficult,
but it's beautiful.

39:33.923 --> 39:35.442
You'll stay the whole day.

39:35.476 --> 39:38.099
You know, you arrive at 2:00,
and you leave at 9:00.

39:38.134 --> 39:40.412
Nice.
So, jefe, what's cooking?

39:40.447 --> 39:42.414
♪

39:42.449 --> 39:45.037
So it's one of the spots
in the fire oven.

39:45.072 --> 39:47.419
Wow. Look at that,
a whole fish baked in salt?

39:47.454 --> 39:48.420
Yes.

39:48.455 --> 39:48.955
♪

39:59.811 --> 40:01.329
Some whole rib eye slabs.

40:01.364 --> 40:02.917
Rib eyes. Wow.

40:02.952 --> 40:04.712
Some suckling pig.
It's not some snack.

40:04.747 --> 40:07.128
That's no snack, man.
That's a meal right there. Wow.

40:07.163 --> 40:08.751
You want to help
in the kitchen, or...

40:08.785 --> 40:10.856
- The carving, yeah, man.
- All right.

40:18.519 --> 40:20.176
Everybody's here.

40:20.210 --> 40:25.112
Fermin, the guys from the
band, Lucia, Federico, Diego,

40:25.146 --> 40:27.977
and it's time to eat.

40:28.011 --> 40:31.290
Oh, yeah.
Come on, it's perfect, right?

40:31.325 --> 40:32.602
Right.

40:32.637 --> 40:34.466
So how long has
this place been here?

40:34.501 --> 40:36.019
Like, about 12 years.

40:36.054 --> 40:38.159
It started as, like,
a shack or a house or a...

40:38.194 --> 40:41.300
It used to be a little house
on the beach with a bar.

40:41.335 --> 40:43.371
You're not allowed
to build here anymore, so

40:43.406 --> 40:47.375
I bought all this land, and
that's the only thing we can do.

40:50.827 --> 40:51.327
♪

40:56.212 --> 40:57.972
- Man, the food is delicious.
- Yeah.

40:58.007 --> 41:01.631
Look at us out here
on a sandbar, middle of nowhere,

41:01.666 --> 41:03.184
eating like gods.

41:03.219 --> 41:06.705
But this is what
I love about Uruguay, no?

41:06.740 --> 41:08.673
Then you suddenly...
You take a drive,

41:08.707 --> 41:10.226
even, like,
one hour and a half...

41:10.260 --> 41:11.641
And you're someplace different.

41:11.676 --> 41:13.298
And you're in a different world.

41:13.332 --> 41:14.672
Good to see. I mean,
this is really exciting here.

41:14.679 --> 41:16.025
I love it here.

41:16.059 --> 41:17.613
Every day he asks,
"Are you sure?"

41:17.647 --> 41:19.373
Every day. Every day.
Hold on. Hold on.

41:19.407 --> 41:21.237
- Do you really love it, Tony?
- Every day.

